Mineral & Resources Corp. (Minorco), a Luxembourg-registered mining and industrial holding company, said its net income in fiscal 1989, ending June 30, rose 6.7% to $280 million from $262.3 million a year earlier. 

Earnings from operations increased to $157.3 million, up 51% from the $103.9 million a year earlier. 

The company disclosed in Johannesburg, South Africa, that per-share earnings in the year rose to $1.64 from $1.54, while the company increased its interim dividend to 14 cents a share from 10 cents a year earlier. 

Minorco is the foreign investment arm of Anglo American Corp. of South Africa Ltd. and has mining and industrial interests in the U.K., North and South America and Australia. 

Anglo American Corp. and De Beers Consolidated Mines Ltd. hold 39.1% and 21%, respectively, of Minorco. 

